 &HT;    Send some good cheer to soldiers
 &HT;    By Staff Reports
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ You can cheer up American soldiers who are stationed
overseas during the holidays. All you have to do is send them a
letter or card. You can tell them how you're going to celebrate or
send them a colorful drawing. Cards will be accepted through Dec.
6. Mail cards for Bosnia and Kosovo to: Any Service Member, I'm
from (list your school, city and state), c/o USPS/Stars and Stripes
Operation Holiday Care Card, Box 153, Unit 29480, APO AE 09211.
</P>
<P>
   NOMINATE A DREAMER
</P>
<P>
   Do you know someone between ages 8 and 15 who has made a
difference in the community? You can nominate him or her to be
among 2,000 Millennium Dreamers. The winners will be recognized by
Walt Disney Co., McDonald's and UNESCO and sent with a parent to
the Walt Disney World resort May 8-10 to share their inspirational
stories. Call 1-888-939-3732 before Dec. 17 for nomination forms
</P>
<P>
   CELEBRATE THE FESTIVAL OF LIGHTS
</P>
<P>
   Click your way through
www.kidsdomain.com/holiday/chanukah/links.html for connections to
more than 10 sites celebrating Hanukkah. Make your own dreidel,
send a virtual latke and learn Hebrew songs for the holiday.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
