<HEADLINE>
`WILD WILD WEST' BAD, BAD; `LIMBO' IS GOOD SAYLES 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By MICHAEL BLOWEN  
 c.1999 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW RELEASES: ``Wild Wild West'' (DVD) _ For fans of the Robert
Conrad-Ross Martin TV show, this feature was especially annoying.
While the show used oxymoronic inventions, it was basically a
character-driven drama. The overloaded special effects in this dud
can't be saved _ even by Will Smith. Some of the TV episodes are
out on video. Rent them instead.
</P>
<P>
   ``Limbo'' _ Director John Sayles was heavily criticized for his
enigmatic ending to this two-souls-in-the-wilderness story, but
that's precisely what makes this film one of his best. David
Strathairn and Mary Elizabeth Mastrantonio are a pair of lost souls
whose inner journey is more dangerous than being lost in Alaska.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   STRAIGHT-TO-VIDEO: Usually, a film released directly to video is
scarred for life, branded as second-rate by consumers. That's
usually justified. But not in the case of ``Bartok the
Magnificent,'' a semi-sequel to the animated ``Anastasia'' (1997).
Bartok is a sharply drawn, witty bat whose vocals are performed by
longtime ``Simpsons'' voicesmith Hank Azaria. The voice of Zozi the
Bear is done by Kelsey Grammer. Fox wisely retained ``Anastasia''
director Don Bluth, and the animation is first-rate. It's so well
crafted, Fox might try releasing it to theaters after its home
video run. That would be a switch.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   COMING ATTRACTIONS: Dec. 7: ``Inspector Gadget,'' ``Strangers in
Good Company'' (DVD). Dec. 14: ``Buena Vista Social Club'' (DVD),
``Drop Dead Gorgeous,'' ``The Harmonists,'' ``The Red Violin''
(DVD), ``Teaching Mrs. Tingle,'' ``The Very Thought of You,'' ``A
Knight in Camelot.'' Dec. 21: ``Run Lola Run'' (DVD), ``American
Pie'' (DVD), ``Tampopo'' (DVD), ``Summer of Sam,'' ``Ethics for the
New Millennium,'' ``A Taxing Woman'' (DVD), ``The Funeral'' (DVD),
``K-911'' (DVD), ``Supercop 2,'' ``Witness to the Mob.'' Dec. 28:
``Dudley Do-Right,'' ``Better Than Chocolate,'' ``Desert Blue''
(DVD). Jan. 4: ``The Thomas Crown Affair'' (DVD), ``Sayonara.''
Jan. 11: ``The Art of Buster Keaton'' (DVD), ``The Extreme
Adventures of Super Dave.'' Jan. 18: ``An Ideal Husband,'' ``The
13th Warrior.'' ``The Wood'' (DVD). Jan. 25: ``Runaway Bride.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
