<P>
   MALAYSIA-ELECT (Kuala Lumpur) _ The grip on power of Prime
Minister Mahathir Mohammed could weaken in the parliamentary
elections on Monday, the most contested ever in Malaysia. By Seth
Mydans.
</P>
<P>
   NIRELAND-CABINET (London) _ Beginning a week in which London
will cede power to the new Northern Ireland government, the
Northern Ireland Assembly, which will run the province, chooses a
Cabinet today. By Warren Hoge.
</P>
<P>
   NAMIBIA-ELECT (Windhoek) _ A decade after winning independence
from the apartheid regime of neighboring South Africa, Namibians
will go to the polls on Tuesday for a national election that will
be a measure of how far the young country has come in pursuit of
political diversity and how far it has to go. By Henri E. Cauvin.
</P>
<P>
   With map.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; WASHINGTON &LR;  (``w'' code)
</P>
