   BUDGET-CLINTON (Washington) _ President Clinton signs the budget
bill. By Richard W. Stevenson.
</P>
<P>
   With
</P>
<P>
   BUDGET-BILL (Washington) _ The budget bill that President
Clinton signed is not the bill that Congress thought it passed.
About 80 percent of the legislative language is missing _ because
of an unusual parliamentary ploy devised by the Senate to shorten
the reading of the bill. By Robert Pear.
</P>
<P>
   SCOTUS-BOYCOTTS (Washington) _ A roundup: The Supreme Court
agrees to hear the case of Massachusetts defending its law banning
the state from doing business with companies doing business with
Burma. New York City has a similar law. Other cases are also
accepted, including one challenging the sentencing provisions of
New Jersey's hate crime law. By Linda Greenhouse.
</P>
<P>
   And
</P>
<P>
   SCOTUS-WHISTLEBLOWERS (Washington) _ The high court hears
arguments in a case challenging the constitutionality of federal
whistle-blower protection laws. By Linda Greenhouse.
