compared with $3.1 billion last year.
</P>
<P>
   Moreover, it is often the wealthiest shoppers that turn to
online shopping, leaving the less prosperous in the malls.
</P>
<P>
   Another study, by the NPD group, offers mall owners some
consoling news, however. Americans are still loathe to buy clothes
via their computers. They want to try them on and touch them. In a
poll taken by NPD, nearly half of all Internet users in the U.S.
said they would never buy clothing online. &QL; 
