   At present the 48 least developed countries account for 0.4
percent of world trade, and their share is shrinking.
</P>
<P>
   The talks could then proceed to two key measures on agriculture.
Export subsidies should be brought under the WTO's anti-dumping
rules and be made subject to a ban. At the same time, the Indian
government's proposal to exempt countries with food deficits from
