<SLUG> BC-ANGELFALLS-HOWTO-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
IF YOU GO TO ANGEL FALLS
</HEADLINE>
 
(EDS: Accompanies ANGEL FALLS) (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   GETTING THERE: Most major airlines fly to Venezuela, and
American Airlines has direct flights there. The flight from the
Dallas/Fort Worth Airport lasts about five hours.
</P>
<P>
   ENTRY: A valid passport and visa or tourist card are required.
Tourist cards are issued on flights from the United States. U.S.
citizens should carry their passports with them at all times.
</P>
<P>
   GETTING AROUND: You can rent a car to explore the region, though
rates tend to be expensive, and robberies aren't unheard of. To get
to other destinations, you may take Avensa or Servivensa, two
domestic airlines.
</P>
<P>
   CURRENCY: The Venezuelan currency is the bolivar, and is written
Bs. In July, the exchange rate was about 600 bolivars to the
dollar, although you should check the exchange rate before going.
U.S. dollars and traveler's checks are widely accepted at the
larger hotels and tourist destinations, although you should carry a
healthy supply of bolivars for smaller purchases and in remote
areas.
</P>
<P>
   TOURS: To get to Angel Falls, you fly into Canaima National
Park. Flights from Venezuela's international airport are readily
available, and an ``air pass'' allows tourists to fly to Canaima,
then to another destination of their choice.
</P>
<P>
   Our three-day, two-night tour cost $200 U.S. per person,
although others in our group haggled the price down by as much as
$75. We used Tiuna Tours, which we booked at the airport from one
of the many tour booths located at the international terminal.
Whichever company you use, make sure the entire tour is outlined
for you, and that you get a receipt.
</P>
<P>
   INFORMATION: The official Web site of the Venezuelan Embassy in
the United States is www.embavenez-us.org. Another helpful site is
Lonely Planet Online, at www.lonelyplanet.com.
</P>
<P>
   The Venezuelan Tourism Association is in Sausalito, Calif.;
(415) 331-0100.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com) nn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
