<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Hokies solidify No. 2 BCS rank
 &HT;    By Tony Barnhart
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Nothing is certain in the wacky world of the Bowl Championship
Series. But on Monday, Virginia Tech (11-0) took another big step
toward playing No. 1 Florida State in the Sugar Bowl for the
national title.
</P>
<P>
   The Hokies, who closed their regular season by thumping Boston
College on Friday, more than doubled their lead over third-place
Nebraska (10-1) in the BCS rankings.
</P>
<P>
   Last week, the second-ranked Hokies held a slim lead of 0.63
points, fueling speculation that once-beaten Nebraska might be able
to leap over them into second place. After Virginia Tech's victory
and Nebraska's 33-30 overtime win over Colorado, the Hokies now
lead the Cornhuskers by 1.54 points.
</P>
<P>
   One of the computer experts has said there is ``no suspense''
concerning Virginia Tech's status in the Sugar Bowl. But others
would say only that the Hokies appear in good shape going into the
final week before the major bowl lineup is determined.
</P>
<P>
   Virginia Tech, the Big East champion, has completed its season;
Nebraska still has to play Saturday against Texas for the Big 12
championship in San Antonio. If Nebraska beats Texas by a big
margin, the Cornhuskers will close that 1.54-point gap in the final
BCS rankings. Whether Nebraska could close it enough to catch
Virginia Tech is not certain.
</P>
<P>
   Last week, when Nebraska was so close to Virginia Tech,
speculation was rampant that the Hokies could get left out of the
big game, despite its record.
</P>
<P>
   But Virginia Tech coach Frank Beamer never wavered.
</P>
<P>
   ``There's too much invested in the BCS, so the two best teams
will play,'' Beamer said. ``I personally think one of those teams
has to be Virginia Tech.''
</P>
<P>
   Virginia Tech never has won a national championship in football,
while Florida State, which has a record of 108-31-1 in the '90s,
will be going for its second title under coach Bobby Bowden.
</P>
<P>
   The final BCS rankings, a formula based on regular polls,
computer rankings, strength of schedule and losses, will be
released Sunday about 4 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   The top two teams in the rankings will play for the national
championship at the Sugar Bowl on Jan. 4. The rest of the BCS bowls
_ the Orange, Rose and Fiesta _ also will be announced Sunday.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
