<HEADLINE>
DO YOUR LASIK-SURGERY HOMEWORK
</HEADLINE>
 
(EDS: Accompanies BC-EYESURGERY) (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By TIM MADIGAN 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   For most, LASIK surgery will be a 15-minute miracle. For a few,
the procedure can be a nightmare. But a knowledgeable patient can
dramatically reduce chances of serious complications. Some consumer
tips:
</P>
<P>
   _ Of the many surgeons performing LASIK, find one with
experience who has performed several hundred LASIK surgeries, at
minimum. Most surgeons performing LASIK have been trained by
companies that manufacture the lasers and microkeratomes, and are
monitored by experienced physicians while performing their first
surgeries. But complication rates generally go down as a surgeon's
experience goes up. Ask about your surgeon's complication rate, and
whether he or she has performed LASIK on other eye doctors, the
most educated consumers.
</P>
<P>
   _ Know your eye. Many experts say that the risk of LASIK
complications increases for people suffering from severe
nearsightedness, farsightedness or astigmatism. Those with
abnormally large pupils or dry eyes can also be considered poor
LASIK candidates. Discuss this thoroughly with your physician if
any of these conditions apply to you.
</P>
<P>
   _ Know the equipment. Does your eye surgeon use a
state-of-the-art microkeratome, the instrument used to create the
corneal flap? Lasers manufactured by the companies Visx of
California and Massachusetts-based Summit Technology are considered
industry standards. Be wary of other brands.
</P>
<P>
   _ Beware of bargains. The most experienced surgeons using the
finest equipment might charge more, but the extra cost will be
worth it. After all, it's your only set of eyes.
</P>
<P>
   _ Hit the Internet. Dozens of Web sites are devoted to LASIK,
including www.surgicaleyes.com, a site composed largely of stories
of LASIK patients with bad experiences.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com) nn
</P>
</TEXT>
