<HEADLINE>
HOT TRAVEL DEALS 
</HEADLINE>
  (For release Sun., Dec. 5) 
(jt) 
 By JANET PIORKO    
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   SHANGHAI SPECIAL _ Pacific Delight Tours has a six-night
Shanghai Supervalue Special package priced from $640 to $770 a
person, double occupancy, from the West Coast; the price is $30
more from New York and most other East Coast cities. It includes
flights on Northwest Airlines; accommodation at the Shanghai Hotel
or the J.C. Mandarin Hotel; daily American breakfast, and a day of
touring. Additional excursions can be added at extra charge. The
tour is offered through March 31. Information: (800) 221-7179.
Reservations are made through travel agents.
</P>
<P>
   ISRAEL AIR FARE _ Wednesday is the last day to purchase El Al's
Early Bird fares from New York to Israel starting at $599. The
fares are valid for travel until Dec. 15 (they are nearly sold out
until then) and from Jan. 10 to March 17. The company is also
offering a Winter Special vacation package through Dec. 18 and from
Jan. 9 to Feb. 29 with Superstar Holidays, starting at $899 from
New York; in addition to air fare, it includes six nights'
accommodation in a choice of four hotels in various parts of the
country. For information or reservations on El Al: (800) 223-6700;
for Superstar Holidays: (800) 352-5786.
</P>
<P>
   SEATTLE'S OFF SEASON _ A program called the Seattle Super Saver
offers discounts of up to 50 percent at 36 downtown hotels through
March 31. Rates for a double room range from $55 (at the Travelodge
by the Space Needle) to $155 (at the Four Seasons Olympic Hotel).
Those who reserve after Jan. 1 get a coupon book with discounts on
attractions, shopping and dining. Reservations can be made through
the individual hotels or by calling (800) 535-7071 from 11:30 a.m.
to 8 p.m. Eastern time from Monday through Friday and 1 to 5 p.m.
on Saturday and Sunday. More information is available on the
Internet, at www.seattlesupersaver.com.
</P>
<P>
   WINTER IN ALSACE _ The city of Strasbourg, in the Alsace region
of France, is the destination of a package from Sabena Airlines,
for travel through Feb. 29, starting at $527 a person, double
occupancy, from New York, Newark or Boston. It is offered
exclusively to American Express cardholders. Travelers fly to
Strasbourg via Brussels _ there are four daily flights connecting
the two cities on weekdays, fewer on weekends _ and spend three
nights at the Strasbourg Hilton or similar hotel. The package
includes daily buffet breakfast, hotel service charge and taxes.
Airport departure taxes and fees of about $50 are extra. The
package is also available, at slightly higher prices, from other
Sabena gateways in the United States (there are seven altogether).
From Chicago, for example, the cost starts at $577; from
Washington, D.C., $547. Tickets must be bought seven days in
advance, and they are nonrefundable. For more information or
reservations: (800) 955-2000.
</P>
