<P>
   Eds., the following story is added to the top of NYT Page 1:
</P>
<P>
   MEXICO-MASSGRAVE (Washington) _ The FBI is sending agents and
forensic experts to Mexico to help dig up the remains of as many as
100 missing U.S. and Mexican citizens who may have been victims of
drug-related murders by Mexico's Juarez drug cartel, a federal law
enforcement official said Monday night. (Summary from wires.)
