<P>
   (NYT26) NEW YORK -- Nov. 29, 1999 -- IMMIG-DETAIN-2, 11-29 --
Nasser Ahmed kisses his five-year old daughter Nagwi as his wife
Salwa Elbayadi looks on Monday night after Ahmed was released from
the Metropolitan Correctional Center in lower Manhattan. At center,
Ahmad, 10, carries his father's belongings. Attorney General Janet
Reno declined to block Ahmed's release Monday night following three
and a half years of detention on secret evidence that the FBI had
said linked him to terrorists in the United States and Egypt.
(Frances Roberts/New York Times)
</P>
