   &UR; POWER _ &LR;  Pacific Gas and Electric Co. made its case before the
California Public Utilities Commission yesterday for a huge rate
increase. Consumer groups, in turn, made their case for why the
state's largest utility should get by with considerably less. The
PUC hearing in San Francisco followed an administrative law judge's
ruling last month that PG&AMP;E should be allowed an annual rate
increase of $243 million. PG&AMP;E had requested $822 million. By DAVID
LAZARUS
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ETRADE _  &LR; E-Trade Group's bid to buy an Internet-based thrift
could be jeopardized by the snail's pace for getting a regulatory
go-ahead, according to documents filed last week with the
Securities and Exchange Commission. By SAM ZUCKERMAN
</P>
<P>
   &UR; CHAMPFUND _  &LR; The 49ers may not be making many points on the
field, but a number of current and former players hope to score big
in another venue: venture capital. Ex-49er greats Harris Barton and
Ronnie Lott yesterday said they have raised $40 million from 99
professional athletes and that their Champion Ventures I fund will
invest it with 10 top technology-focused venture capital funds. By
PETER SINTON
</P>
<P>
   &UR; MONEYBAG _  &LR; I would like to take some money out of one of my
individual retirement accounts and convert it to a Roth IRA (I
don't have one yet). However, I don't know whether I am permitted
to do this, because I don't have any wage income. All I have is
nontaxable disability income, dividends and interest. By ARTHUR
LOUIS
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
